---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Career">
  <div class="post-content relative z-10 bg-white lg:pt-[272px] pt-[140px]">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="post-content-title text-center max-w-[792px] mx-auto text-white">
                <p class="text-sm font-medium tracking-[0.16em] uppercase">INTRODUCING</p>
                <h1 class="post-content-title font-anton lg:text-[100px] md:text-[80px] text-[50px] lg:mt-[78px] mt-[30px]">FARYNGROVE</h1>
                <p class="font-text text-[#AEAEAE] lg:mt-[63px] mt-[30px]">A fantastical open-world map set on an intricately designed floating island. Explore hidden easter eggs and captivating landmarks scattered throughout this immersive environment, crafted exclusively for Fortnite players.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="post-thumbnail lg:mt-[96px] mt-[30px] after:content-[''] after:block after:pt-[60%] relative overflow-hidden rounded-[15px]">
                <img src="/images/ourwork-1.png" alt="" class="absolute top-0 left-0 w-full h-full object-cover">
            </div>
            <div class="post-stage-list">
                <div class="post-stage-item">
                    <div class="post-stage-content border-b border-[#000]">
                        <h3 class="font-be text-black text-[17px] tracking-[0.17em] uppercase font-normal post-stage-content-title mb-8">First stage - DEFINING THE GOALS</h3>
                        <div class="grid grid-cols-12 md:gap-x-20 gap-y-10">
                            <div class="md:col-span-7 col-span-12 flex flex-col gap-y-4 text-black font-display leading-[1.3] lg:text-[30px] text-[18px] font-medium">
                                <p>The aim of this Fortnite map is to seamlessly integrate medieval and fantasy elements within a vast open-world layout, elevating player engagement through a dynamic setting that accommodates multiple game modes, including team battles. The design incorporates both indoor and outdoor areas, enriching the gameplay experience with versatile strategies and hidden Easter eggs to discover.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="md:col-span-5 col-span-12">
                                <div class="game-feature">
                                    <p>Crafting a Mockup of the Game</p>
                                    <p>Fantasy Themed Map</p>
                                    <p>Multiplayer Focus</p>
                                </div>
                                <div class="py-8 mt-8 border-t border-[#000] flex flex-col gap-y-5 font-inter text-sm leading-[1.5] text-black font-light">
                                   <div class="item">
                                        <p>The following elements were highlighted:</p>
                                   </div>
                                   <div class="item">
                                        <p><b>Vertical Mountain: </b></p>
                                        <p>
                                            Ascending mountain with multiple villages and roads that connect the entire map.
                                        </p>
                                   </div>
                                   <div class="item">
                                        <p><b>Secondary Areas: </b></p>
                                        <p>
                                            The development of internal areas such as caves or the inside of each village home to increase the versatility of the map.
                                        </p>
                                   </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="post-stage-item">
                    <div class="post-stage-gallery owl-carousel">
                        <div class="post-stage-gallery-item">
                            <a href="/images/ourwork-1.png" data-fancybox="gallery">
                                <img src="/images/post-stage-image.png" alt="">
                            </a>
                        </div>
                        <div class="post-stage-gallery-item">
                            <a href="/images/ourwork-1.png" data-fancybox="gallery">
                                <img src="/images/post-stage-image.png" alt="">
                            </a>
                        </div>
                        <div class="post-stage-gallery-item">
                            <a href="/images/ourwork-1.png" data-fancybox="gallery">
                                <img src="/images/post-stage-image.png" alt="">
                            </a>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="post-stage-content border-b border-[#000]">
                        <h3 class="font-be text-black text-[17px] tracking-[0.17em] uppercase font-normal post-stage-content-title mb-8">Second stage - Initial concept</h3>
                        <div class="grid grid-cols-12 md:gap-x-20 gap-y-10">
                            <div class="md:col-span-7 col-span-12 flex flex-col gap-y-4 text-black font-inter leading-[1.5] text-[14px] font-light">
                                <p>The project's initial concept for the Faryngrove map in Fortnite started with the conceptualization of the environment and the style of the village.
                                </p>
                                <p>After that the positions of the different area according to the various levels of the map.
                                </p>
                                <p>Last phase was the brainstorm of details such as the "Fishing Mechanism on the lake", various Loot Chests and other interesting elements that would enhance the gameplay of this Fortnite map.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="md:col-span-5 col-span-12">
                                <div class="game-feature">
                                    <p>Crafting a Mockup of the Game</p>
                                    <p>Fantasy Themed Map</p>
                                    <p>Multiplayer Focus</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="post-stage-item">
                    <div class="post-stage-gallery owl-carousel">
                        <div class="post-stage-gallery-item">
                            <a href="/images/ourwork-1.png" data-fancybox="gallery">
                                <img src="/images/post-stage-image.png" alt="">
                            </a>
                        </div>
                        <div class="post-stage-gallery-item">
                            <a href="/images/ourwork-1.png" data-fancybox="gallery">
                                <img src="/images/post-stage-image.png" alt="">
                            </a>
                        </div>
                        <div class="post-stage-gallery-item">
                            <a href="/images/ourwork-1.png" data-fancybox="gallery">
                                <img src="/images/post-stage-image.png" alt="">
                            </a>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="post-stage-content border-b border-[#000]">
                        <h3 class="font-be text-black text-[17px] tracking-[0.17em] uppercase font-normal post-stage-content-title mb-8">Third stage - Development</h3>
                        <div class="grid grid-cols-12 md:gap-x-20 gap-y-10">
                            <div class="md:col-span-7 col-span-12 flex flex-col gap-y-4 text-black font-inter leading-[1.5] text-[14px] font-light">
                                <p>The development stage of the Fortnite map Faryngrove, in UEFN (Unreal Engine for Fortnite), started with the development of the basis of the island, followed by the creation of the main areas on the surface like the Village and roads layout and subsequently assets and elements on the exteriors and interiors, such as caves and inside of the houses, were developed.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="md:col-span-5 col-span-12">
                                <div class="game-feature">
                                    <p>Development Process Starts</p>
                                    <p>Weekly Update Call</p>
                                    <p>Feedback Implementation</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="post-stage-item">
                    <div class="post-stage-content">
                       <div class="grid grid-cols-12 md:gap-10 gap-0">
                            <div class="md:col-span-5 col-span-12">
                                <h3 class="font-be text-black text-[17px] tracking-[0.17em] uppercase font-normal post-stage-content-title mb-8">FINAL stage - Delivery</h3>
                            </div>
                            <div class="md:col-span-7 col-span-12 text-black font-inter leading-[1.5] text-[14px] font-light">
                                <p>After many weeks of work Metatheory Studio team is proud to have completed the development of Faryngrove map in Fortnite, hitting all of the targets that have been highlighted at the beginning of the project.</p>
                            </div>
                       </div>
                        
                    </div>
                    <div class="post-stage-carousel">
                        <div class= "post-stage-carousel__main owl-carousel">
                            <div class="item-slide">
                                <img src="/images/main-stage.png" alt="">
                            </div>
                            <div class="item-slide">
                                <img src="/images/main-stage.png" alt="">
                            </div>
                            <div class="item-slide">
                                <img src="/images/main-stage.png" alt="">
                            </div>
                            <div class="item-slide">
                                <img src="/images/main-stage.png" alt="">
                            </div>
                            <div class="item-slide">
                                <img src="/images/main-stage.png" alt="">
                            </div>
                            <div class="item-slide">
                                <img src="/images/main-stage.png" alt="">
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="post-stage-carousel__thumb owl-carousel">
                            <div class="item-slide">
                                    <img src="/images/main-stage.png" alt="">
                                </div>
                                <div class="item-slide">
                                    <img src="/images/main-stage.png" alt="">
                                </div>
                                <div class="item-slide">
                                    <img src="/images/main-stage.png" alt="">
                                </div>
                                <div class="item-slide">
                                    <img src="/images/main-stage.png" alt="">
                                </div>
                                <div class="item-slide">
                                    <img src="/images/main-stage.png" alt="">
                                </div>
                                <div class="item-slide">
                                    <img src="/images/main-stage.png" alt="">
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<script src="./vendor/gsap/gsap.min.js" defer></script>
<script src="./vendor/gsap/scrollSmoother.min.js" defer></script>
<script src="./vendor/swiper/swiper-bundle.min.js" defer></script>
<script src="./js/fancybox.js" defer></script>
<script src="./js/pages/postDetail.js" defer></script>
